cs.DL, cs.IR, cs.WEB, cs.CL, cs.HC 

This paper deals with the parsing and analysis of Wikipedia's revision history, which involves natural language processing, web technologies, and human-computer interaction. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.DL (Digital Libraries), cs.IR (Information Retrieval), and cs.WEB (Web Technologies). Additionally, the paper discusses the expansion of macros in historical article revisions, which involves computational linguistics and natural language processing, making cs.CL (Computation and Language) another likely sub-category. Finally, the paper also analyzes the importance of hyperlinks for user navigation, which falls under the sub-category of cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction).
